sql:
SELECT country_id, english_name, area_sq_km 
FROM countries 
WHERE area_sq_km > (SELECT AVG(area_sq_km) FROM countries);

external_knowledge:
- Significant number of residents: More than 100,000,000 people;
- Economic richness per person: Refers to GDP per capita;
- Financial might: Refers to the total GDP of the region;
- Sheer number of inhabitants: Refers to the total population of the region.

- "Caught the demographic growth wave" metaphorically refers to significant population increase;
- "Leaping into a new era" metaphorically indicates a substantial change;
- "Population increase of more than a million" refers to the condition where the population change is greater than 1,000,000;
- "From 2010 to 2020" specifies the time frame over which the population change is measured.

